<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Valsu_01</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">does this spell strip all buffs?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">No.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aumaar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Divine Intervention is an upgrade to the level 51 Death Pact.  The problem is it uses 2 Emeralds and only lasts 10min with a 5min recast time.<P>Basically its only used for those special uber mobs before the MA charges.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">2 min recast time.  And assuming you remember (still only had the spell a month or 2 so I forget), its definitely worth casting.<P>One time DI went off after I had died.  Nothing like doing a dead CH :></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just in case anyone forgot. I tested DI a bit a while ago and posted the result - you can still find my post here somewhere but I am too lazy to dig it up.<P>Anyway - in 50 casts I had it work 20 times with 78 cha (cha is said to have some effect).<P>Today I did 20 casts and it work 7 times with 180 cha.<P>So, sofar I wouldnt say CHA appears to matter.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bertil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Only being 58 I have had no contact with this, but, is it the norm that people cast DI on your MT ?<P>With the Likes of Focus/Avatar proc, Aego, buff space isnt so much of a premium as it used to be, do people consider this worthwhile ?<P>Also, what happens to the agro ? Is the DI regarded as a CH (if it takes, obviously), and the tank keeps agro, or does the tank effectively die, reducing agro to ZERO, thus mob turning on the next highest people on the agro list and tear all your Wizards/Rogues to pieces ?<P>Bertil Mithrilmane <Dark Templars><BR>58th Templar of Brell<BR>Xegony<P>Tenor Songtwister <Dark Templars><BR>58th Troubadour of Tunare<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tank keeps aggro normally and noone gets aggro from the "DI-CH" as far as I can tell/imagine. <P>We rarely do (hard for us) uber fights without casting DI on the MT(s) - and it has definitely saved the day more than once. For stuff thats a sure win we often skip it though out of lazyness. The cost to cast it isnt a concern at all.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rendorr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DI is basically a free cheal, if it works.  All buffs are left intact.  Cast DI on your main tanks before a big fight.  The spell seems to do a check against the recipient's cha, not the caster's.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rendorr<P>Wrt checking the recipients CHA.<P>I would love to see any tests you have done on that if possible. My tests were done casting on myself - with 78 cha I got 20/50, with 180 cha I got 7/20 (I know, a pretty short trial). So, this admitting short test definitely doesnt seem to imply a significant increase in success with CHA.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In the previous thread on DI/DP, the person who designed the spell at VI is quoted as saying that it is the target's CHA at the time of the "firing" of the spell that is relevant, not the caster's. Which makes sense from a game engine perspective-otherwise they would have to track who cast the spell...what happens if that person logs out/dies? do you use their CHA at the time the spell was cast (in which case they could just stack CHA gear on for the casting, then remove it immediately) or at the time the spell tries to fire? Using the CHA of the target makes alot more sense...<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Templar of the 55th Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Smith (183) Master Brewer (175) Master Potter (168) Master Tailor (163)Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) <BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aye, it definitely only makes sense to use the stats (cha) of the target at the time DI is to heal or not.<P>However, as my (admittingly short) test reveals there isnt an obvious gain from 78 cha to 180 cha. Note, that I cast on myself - so the target had 180 cha at all times for no gain. So, unless someone else posts a test with a different result I am inclined to believe that the effect of CHA is rather insignificant if any.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/shrug<P>All my successful uses of DP have been when the target had a CHA buff, my unsuccessful ones have been when they didn't. Very small sample base, tho.<P>My guess, it has about as much affect on it firing as AGI has on AC...only a few percentage points either way.<P>I just figure, with Focus and Aego around now, buff spots aren't near the premium-I'd rather have my MA have a CHA buff he didn't really need than not have one he did.<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Templar of the 55th Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Smith (183) Master Brewer (175) Master Potter (168) Master Tailor (163)Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) <BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre